          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " At the lowest two bombarding energies gamma-",
                "rays were detected in an array of five 12.7 cm long",
                "by 12.7 cm diameter detectors at 20.5 cm from the",
                "target. The detectors were periodically moved in a",
                "cyclic way such that each detector was placed at each",
                "detection angle for about the same period of time."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " At bombarding energies of Ealpha=15.54 and",
                "16.35 MeV gamma-rays were detected in two large-",
                "volume Ge(Li) counters, which were moved through the",
                "same set of detection angles. In this case a fixed",
                "NaI(Li) detector served as a monitor. Gamma-rays",
                "coincident with neutrons were detected at 45,90 and",
                "135 degr. to the beam direction."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons in coincidence with gamma-rays were",
                "detected in a liquid-scintillator neutron detector",
                "placed at 0+-3.5 degr. to the beam direction and at",
                "150 cm from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 24Mg target, enriched to 99.94%,was self-supporting",
                "with a thickness of 250 ug/cm2 and other 24Mg target",
                "was used with a thickness of 100 ug/cm2 evaporated on",
                "a 5 mu-m thick Au foil."
              ]
            }
